25|$|Terence Marne O'Neill, Baron O'Neill of the Maine, PC (10 September 1914 – 12 June 1990) was {{the fourth}} Prime Minister of Northern Ireland and leader (1963–1969) of the Ulster Unionist Party (UUP). A {{moderate}} unionist, who sought to reconcile the sectarian divisions in Northern Ireland society, he was Member of the Parliament of Northern Ireland for the Bannside constituency from 1946 until his forced resignation in April 1969 as <b>communal</b> <b>conflict</b> erupted; his successor in Parliament was Ian Paisley, while control of the UUP also passed to more hard-line elements.|$|E
